msgid "Tips"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:10
#: 47ae7a2135f84b3c8c069a07e2ca180b
msgid "If using qubes-vpn, check the VPN service’s log in the VPN VM by running:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:18
#: 0ef94f16a5224aceb4407dd4ed162e17
msgid "Always test your basic VPN connection before adding scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:20
#: 9dad49d45a9c433497f028e33d6baa43
msgid ""
"Test DNS: Ping a familiar domain name from an appVM. It should print the "
"IP address for the domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:22
#: a80c58db99af4e0996cddb3f1d364df7
msgid ""
"Use ``iptables -L -v`` and ``iptables -L -v -t nat`` to check firewall "
"rules. The latter shows the critical PR-QBS chain that enables DNS "
"forwarding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:27
#: c1513bf663564268b3e78d1b1d8b6ac3
msgid "VPN does not reconnect after suspend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:30
#: 934e8e47599e4273bd84a6af13b4a4d5
msgid "This applies when using OpenVPN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:32
#: a334fc00e2064dfaa44fc8e7d33a3ed0
msgid ""
"After suspend/resume, OpenVPN may not automatically reconnect. In order "
"to get it to work, you must kill the OpenVPN process and restart it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:35
#: 976c671518974a6f86878922065dfd15
msgid "VPN stuck at \"Ready to start link\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:38
#: 2419961eae6f4826a2da2e8d6c85be3b
msgid ""
"After setting up OpenVPN and restarting the VM, you may be repeatedly "
"getting the popup “Ready to start link”, but the VPN isn’t connected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:40
#: 2b16e7a71e7b4be49bfaa0b24e4dedec
msgid ""
"To figure out the root of the problem, check the VPN logs in "
"``/var/log/syslog`` or use ``journalctl``. The logs may reveal issues "
"like missing OpenVPN libraries, which you can then install."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:43
#: 1016cc44fc0649be9bce6b5b316ee067
msgid "``notify-send`` induced failure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:46
#: 3356a9f3e30749ed8276a7e3473ba008
msgid ""
"`Some VPN guides <https://forum.qubes-os.org/t/configuring-a-proxyvm-vpn-"
"gateway/19061>`__ use complex scripts that include a call to ``notify-"
"send``, yet some images may not contain this tool or may not have it "
"working properly. For instance calling ``notify-send`` on a ``fedora-36``"
" template VM gives:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:54
#: 1d4a7d94d209446c9ece10845f5f761c
msgid "To check this tool is working properly run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:61
#: 18e5b162102b4183ac1dc08462b8f965
msgid ""
"You should see the ``info`` message appear on the top of your screen. If "
"that is the case then ``notify-send`` is not the issue. If it is not, and"
" you have an error of some sort you can:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:63
#: 11366317f64940f5a9f677ebfc6020a3
msgid ""
"Remove all calls to ``notify-send`` from scripts you are using to start "
"VPN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vpn-troubleshooting.rst:65
#: efc46f2602be4dc9b2b4919505963696
msgid ""
"Use another template qube that has a working ``notify-send`` or find "
"proper guide and make your current template run ``notify-send`` work "
"properly."
msgstr ""

